      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, please don't apologize. It takes real courage to say this out loud, and I'm genuinely glad you told me. You haven't let anyone down — you've just given us the information we actually need to help you move forward properly.\n\nI have to be straight with you, though, on one important point:\n\n---\n\n**I can't diagnose what's happening or tell you how to treat it.** That's not me being evasive — it's that plantar fasciitis that has worsened to the point of stopping you mid-run is a medical situation, and getting it wrong could mean months more off your feet. You need eyes (and hands) on this from your physiotherapist or a sports medicine doctor. Given that you've described significant worsening and pain that's stopping your runs, I'd encourage you to contact them **this week** — ideally in the next day or two.\n\nWhen you go, be honest with them exactly the way you were just honest with me. Tell them you ran through the pain, that it's gotten worse, and describe exactly when and where it hurts. That information is gold for them.\n\n---\n\n**Here's what happens with your training plan right now:**\n\nI'm pausing your plan completely. Not as a punishment — but because continuing to run on a worsening injury without medical clearance would be the wrong thing for me to recommend, and I won't do it.\n\nYour physiotherapist previously cleared you for 20 minutes of easy running. That clearance was based on your condition at that time. Given what you've described, we need a fresh assessment and updated clearance before we run another step.\n\n---\n\n**What I'd like you to do:**\n\n1. **Book your physio appointment today.** Show them your training log if it helps.\n2. **Rest from running until you've seen them.** Walking, swimming, or cycling may be fine — ask them.\n3. **Come back and tell me what they say.** The moment you have updated guidance, we rebuild together. Your VDOT, your fitness, your goal — none of that disappears. We just protect the foundation first.\n\n---\n\nYou've done real work these past few weeks, James. The runs in your log show consistency and patience. That doesn't go away. The path back to running well runs *through* this appointment, not around it.\n\nI'll be here when you're ready. \uD83D\uDCAA"
        }
      ],
